Add a "here be dragons" comment? Re-materialization of const member variables means that a const mirror pointer may not be updated by a read barrier. Generally we've avoided making such member variables const, here there is a reliance on no thread suspension. Perhaps assert that no thread suspension is allowable in the constructor.

